StrategoXT 0.11 -- released July 16, 2004

---------++ Summary of Changes

   * Separate compilation ready for use

   * Many deployment improvements
     * Cygwin and Mac OS X Support (really!)
     * Reduced size of distributions
     * Check dependencies at configure-time

   * XML Support

   * Upgrade of SDF packages

   * New tool: parenthesize generator, improves the support for the
     implementation of pretty-printers.

   * Global choice operator is now much easier to use. You won't need
     a separate StrategoXT installation to use the global choice.

   * New strategies in the Stratego library:
      * stateful sets
      * filtering text files
      * new-name: generate unique names with a prefix

   * Many bug-fixes, e.g.
      * fixed a bug that causes crashes in large XTC tools
      * improvements of new dynamic rules
      * mutual recursive lets

   * Related releases:
      * JavaFront
      * StrategoShell (interpreter!)
      * Tiger

---------++ Separate Compilation

   * Now actually works
   * Also for XTC tools
   * See HowTo at Wiki

   * Dynamic linking
      * libtool

   * Size of distribution

